### OpenRouter Proxy — Request Payloads (all scenarios)
### Compatible with VS Code REST Client / IntelliJ HTTP Client
### Base URL: http://localhost:8000
### ============================================================


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 1. Health Check
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET http://localhost:8000/
Content-Type: application/json

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 2. List Available Tools
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET http://localhost:8000/tools
Content-Type: application/json

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 3. Basic Chat — Non-Streaming
### Simple question, no tools, returns full JSON response
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the capital of France?"
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 20. Tiny Benchmark — List Scenarios
### No external benchmark package required.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET http://localhost:8000/benchmarks/tiny/scenarios
Content-Type: application/json

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 21. Tiny Benchmark — Run All Scenarios
### Returns total, passed, failed, score, and per-case details.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/benchmarks/tiny/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "temperature": 0,
  "max_tokens": 300
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 22. Tiny Benchmark — Run Selected Scenarios
### Available IDs: basic_capital, weather_tool, email_tool
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/benchmarks/tiny/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "scenario_ids": ["weather_tool", "email_tool"],
  "temperature": 0,
  "max_tokens": 300
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 4. Basic Chat — Streaming (SSE)
### Returns token-by-token chunks for spinner/loading support
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Count from 1 to 5."
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 5. Chat with System Prompt — Non-Streaming
### Custom system prompt to control behavior
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a pirate. Respond to everything in pirate speak."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tell me about the weather today."
    }
  ],
  "temperature": 0.9,
  "max_tokens": 200
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 6. Chat with System Prompt — Streaming
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a concise technical assistant. Keep answers under 3 sentences."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Explain what a REST API is."
    }
  ],
  "stream": true,
  "temperature": 0.3,
  "max_tokens": 150
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 7. Multi-Turn Conversation — Non-Streaming
### Passing conversation history
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a helpful assistant."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My name is Jaydip."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nice to meet you, Jaydip! How can I help you today?"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is my name?"
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 8. Tool Calling — Weather (Non-Streaming)
### LLM decides to call get_weather, proxy executes it
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the weather in Mumbai right now?"
    }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "city": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "The city name to get weather for"
            }
          },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 9. Tool Calling — Weather (Streaming)
### Same as above but with token-by-token streaming response
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the weather in Delhi?"
    }
  ],
  "stream": true,
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "city": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "The city name to get weather for"
            }
          },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 10. Tool Calling — Email (Non-Streaming)
### LLM decides to call generate_email
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Write a formal email to john@example.com about the project deadline extension."
    }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "generate_email",
        "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "to": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Email recipient address"
            },
            "subject": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Email subject line"
            },
            "tone": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Tone of the email (e.g. formal, casual)",
              "default": "formal"
            }
          },
          "required": ["to", "subject"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 11. Multiple Tools — LLM Chooses Which to Use
### Both tools provided, LLM picks the right one
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the weather in Surat?"
    }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "city": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "The city name to get weather for"
            }
          },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "generate_email",
        "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "to": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Email recipient address"
            },
            "subject": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Email subject line"
            },
            "tone": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Tone of the email (e.g. formal, casual)"
            }
          },
          "required": ["to", "subject"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 12. Forced Tool Choice — tool_choice
### Force the LLM to use a specific tool
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tell me about Jaipur"
    }
  ],
  "tool_choice": {
    "type": "function",
    "function": {
      "name": "get_weather"
    }
  },
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "city": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "The city name to get weather for"
            }
          },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 13. No Tool Choice — tool_choice: "none"
### Prevent the LLM from using any tools even if provided
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the weather in London?"
    }
  ],
  "tool_choice": "none",
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "city": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "The city name to get weather for"
            }
          },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 14. Custom Model Parameters
### Temperature, max_tokens, top_p, stop, penalties
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Write a creative one-liner about programming."
    }
  ],
  "temperature": 1.2,
  "max_tokens": 100,
  "top_p": 0.95,
  "frequency_penalty": 0.5,
  "presence_penalty": 0.3
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 15. Stop Sequences
### LLM stops generating at the specified sequence
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "List the first 10 prime numbers, one per line."
    }
  ],
  "stop": ["7"],
  "max_tokens": 200
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 16. Default Model — No model specified
### Uses DEFAULT_MODEL from .env (meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hello! What model are you?"
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 17. Different Model — GPT-4o Mini
### Using a different OpenRouter model
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Say hello in one sentence."
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 18. Minimal Payload — Bare minimum required fields
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hi"
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 19. Full Payload — All Parameters Combined
### Everything together: system prompt, tools, streaming, params
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/v1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a helpful assistant that uses tools when appropriate. Be concise."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the weather in Ahmedabad and also draft me an email to boss@company.com about taking a day off tomorrow."
    }
  ],
  "stream": true,
  "temperature": 0.7,
  "max_tokens": 500,
  "top_p": 0.9,
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "city": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "The city name to get weather for"
            }
          },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "generate_email",
        "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "to": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Email recipient address"
            },
            "subject": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Email subject line"
            },
            "tone": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Tone of the email (e.g. formal, casual)",
              "default": "formal"
            }
          },
          "required": ["to", "subject"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
